{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Run two isolated OpenClaw AI agent instances on a single Mac — each with its own workspace, channels, and API keys."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/openclaw.ai"},{"text":" is an open-source self-hosted AI assistant","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that connects to Claude, GPT-4, Gemini, and other models. Running OpenClaw","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in macOS VMs with Spooktacular gives you:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Isolation"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — each instance has its own macOS environment, API keys,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and workspace. A misconfigured agent can’t affect the other.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"2 instances per Mac"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — Apple Silicon’s 2-VM kernel limit maps","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"perfectly to running a pair of agents (e.g., work + personal,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"or production + staging).","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Snapshots"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — save a working OpenClaw configuration, experiment,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and roll back if something breaks.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Kubernetes-managed"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — scale OpenClaw instances across a fleet","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of Macs using ","type":"text"},{"code":"MacOSVMPool","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Prerequisites","level":3,"text":"Prerequisites"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Apple Silicon Mac (M1 or later)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"macOS 14+ on the host","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Spooktacular installed (","type":"text"},{"code":"brew install --cask spooktacular","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":")","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"API key from Anthropic, OpenAI, or Google","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Quick-Start-Two-OpenClaw-Instances","level":2,"text":"Quick Start: Two OpenClaw Instances"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"1-Create-the-first-VM","level":3,"text":"1. Create the first VM"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["spook create openclaw-work --from-ipsw latest \\","    --cpu 4 --memory 8 --disk 32 \\","    --network nat \\","    --user-data .\/setup-openclaw.sh \\","    --provision disk-inject"]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"2-Clone-for-the-second-instance","level":3,"text":"2. Clone for the second instance"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["spook clone openclaw-work openclaw-personal"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The clone takes ~50ms (APFS copy-on-write). Each VM gets a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"unique machine identifier automatically.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"3-Start-both","level":3,"text":"3. Start both"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["spook start openclaw-work --headless","spook start openclaw-personal --headless"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Both VMs boot and run OpenClaw independently. Each listens","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"on its own IP address, port 18789.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"4-Check-status","level":3,"text":"4. Check status"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["spook list","spook ip openclaw-work","spook ip openclaw-personal"]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"User-Data-Script-for-OpenClaw","level":2,"text":"User-Data Script for OpenClaw"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Create a script that installs and configures OpenClaw automatically:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["#!\/bin\/bash","# setup-openclaw.sh — installs OpenClaw in a macOS VM","","set -euo pipefail","","# Install Homebrew (if not present)","if ! command -v brew &>\/dev\/null; then","    \/bin\/bash -c \"$(curl -fsSL https:\/\/raw.githubusercontent.com\/Homebrew\/install\/HEAD\/install.sh)\"","    eval \"$(\/opt\/homebrew\/bin\/brew shellenv)\"","fi","","# Install Node.js 24","brew install node@24","echo 'export PATH=\"\/opt\/homebrew\/opt\/node@24\/bin:$PATH\"' >> ~\/.zshrc","export PATH=\"\/opt\/homebrew\/opt\/node@24\/bin:$PATH\"","","# Install OpenClaw","npm install -g openclaw@latest","","# Run onboard with daemon installation","# (The API key should be set via environment variable or","#  injected via the shared folder)","openclaw onboard --install-daemon","","echo \"OpenClaw installed and running on port 18789\""]},{"type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For production deployments, pass the API key via","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a shared folder or environment variable rather than","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"hardcoding it in the script.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note","style":"note"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Passing-API-Keys-Securely","level":3,"text":"Passing API Keys Securely"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use a shared folder to deliver configuration without","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"embedding secrets in the script:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["# On the host: create a config directory","mkdir -p ~\/openclaw-configs\/work","cat > ~\/openclaw-configs\/work\/openclaw.json << 'EOF'","{","    \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250514\",","    \"anthropicApiKey\": \"sk-ant-your-key-here\"","}","EOF","","# Create VM with shared folder","spook create openclaw-work --from-ipsw latest \\","    --share ~\/openclaw-configs\/work:config:ro \\","    --user-data .\/setup-openclaw.sh"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In the setup script, copy the config from the shared folder:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["# Inside setup-openclaw.sh","mkdir -p ~\/.openclaw","cp \"\/Volumes\/My Shared Files\/openclaw.json\" ~\/.openclaw\/openclaw.json","openclaw config validate"]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Kubernetes-OpenClaw-Fleet","level":2,"text":"Kubernetes: OpenClaw Fleet"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Deploy OpenClaw instances across multiple Macs using","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the Kubernetes operator:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"yaml","code":["apiVersion: spooktacular.io\/v1alpha1","kind: MacOSVMPool","metadata:","  name: openclaw-agents","  namespace: ai","spec:","  replicas: 2","  image: ghcr.io\/spooktacular\/macos:15.4","","  provisioning:","    mode: disk-inject","    userData: |","      #!\/bin\/bash","      brew install node@24","      export PATH=\"\/opt\/homebrew\/opt\/node@24\/bin:$PATH\"","      npm install -g openclaw@latest","      mkdir -p ~\/.openclaw","      # Config injected via K8s secret → shared folder","      cp \"\/Volumes\/My Shared Files\/openclaw.json\" ~\/.openclaw\/","      openclaw onboard --install-daemon","","  resources:","    cpu: 4","    memory: 8Gi","    disk: 32Gi","","  network:","    mode: nat"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Each Mac in the fleet runs 2 OpenClaw VMs. Ten Macs =","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"20 OpenClaw instances.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Networking-Between-Instances","level":2,"text":"Networking Between Instances"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If your OpenClaw instances need to communicate (e.g.,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a coordinator agent delegating to worker agents):","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["spook create openclaw-coordinator --from-ipsw latest --network nat","spook create openclaw-worker --from-ipsw latest --network nat"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"NAT networking lets the VMs reach each other via their","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"DHCP-assigned IPs and the host Mac. The coordinator can","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"reach the worker’s gateway on port 18789. Use","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"NetworkMode\/isolated","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" if you need to prevent internet","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"access entirely, communicating through shared folders","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and the VirtIO socket instead.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For internet access + inter-VM communication, use","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"NAT networking — both VMs can reach each other via","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"their NAT-assigned IPs.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Resource-Planning","level":2,"text":"Resource Planning"},{"type":"table","rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Setup","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"CPU","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Memory","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Disk","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Notes","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Cloud models only","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"4 cores","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"4 GB","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"16 GB","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Minimal — OpenClaw is lightweight","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Cloud + light local models","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"4 cores","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"8 GB","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"32 GB","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Ollama with small models","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Heavy local models (Llama 3)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"6 cores","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"16 GB","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"64 GB","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Needs unified memory","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]],"header":"row"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Since macOS VMs share the host’s unified memory via","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the Virtualization framework, the GPU (Metal) is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"available inside the VM for local model inference.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Monitoring","level":2,"text":"Monitoring"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Check OpenClaw health in each VM:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["# From the host","spook ssh openclaw-work -- \"openclaw status\"","spook ssh openclaw-personal -- \"openclaw status\"","","# Or via the gateway API","curl http:\/\/$(spook ip openclaw-work):18789\/health","curl http:\/\/$(spook ip openclaw-personal):18789\/health"]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Snapshots","level":2,"text":"Snapshots"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Save a working OpenClaw configuration before making changes.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The VM must be stopped to take or restore a disk-level snapshot:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["spook stop openclaw-work","spook snapshot openclaw-work pre-upgrade","spook start openclaw-work --headless","# ... make changes, install new version ...","# If something breaks:","spook stop openclaw-work","spook restore openclaw-work pre-upgrade","spook start openclaw-work --headless"]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/OpenClawGuide"},"kind":"article","sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/openclawguide"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"role":"collectionGroup","title":"Running OpenClaw in Virtual Machines"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Guides","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CLIReference","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GitHubActionsGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/JenkinsGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning"],"title":"Guides"}],"references":{"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/RemoteDesktop":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Connect to Spooktacular VMs via VNC for remote development, QA testing, and design review."}],"title":"Remote Desktop Access","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/remotedesktop","role":"collectionGroup","kind":"article","type":"topic"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","abstract":[{"text":"Create and manage macOS virtual machines on Apple Silicon.","type":"text"}],"role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit","title":"SpooktacularKit","type":"topic","kind":"symbol"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/CLIReference":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CLIReference","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Manage macOS virtual machines from the terminal with the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook"},{"type":"text","text":" CLI."}],"title":"Using the spook Command-Line Interface","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/clireference","role":"collectionGroup","kind":"article","type":"topic"},"https://openclaw.ai":{"type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OpenClaw"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/openclaw.ai","title":"OpenClaw","url":"https:\/\/openclaw.ai"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/GettingStarted":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create your first macOS virtual machine in minutes."}],"title":"Getting Started with Spooktacular","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/gettingstarted","role":"collectionGroup","kind":"article","type":"topic"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/EC2MacDeployment":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Run Spooktacular on AWS EC2 Mac dedicated hosts to double your macOS CI capacity."}],"title":"Deploying on EC2 Mac","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/ec2macdeployment","role":"collectionGroup","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","kind":"article","type":"topic"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/KubernetesGuide":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Manage macOS virtual machines as Kubernetes resources using the MacOSVM custom resource definition."}],"title":"Kubernetes Integration","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/kubernetesguide","role":"collectionGroup","kind":"article","type":"topic"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/JenkinsGuide":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/JenkinsGuide","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Run Jenkins build agents in Spooktacular VMs for iOS and macOS CI\/CD."}],"title":"Configuring Jenkins Nodes","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/jenkinsguide","role":"collectionGroup","kind":"article","type":"topic"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/Versioning":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Understand what version numbers mean and what to expect from each release."}],"title":"Versioning & Release Schedule","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/versioning","role":"collectionGroup","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning","kind":"article","type":"topic"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/MLWorkloads":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Run ML training and inference on Apple Silicon GPUs inside Spooktacular virtual machines."}],"role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/mlworkloads","title":"Machine Learning Workloads","kind":"article","type":"topic"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/GitHubActionsGuide":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GitHubActionsGuide","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Run self-hosted macOS GitHub Actions runners in Spooktacular VMs with ephemeral isolation and automatic scaling."}],"url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/githubactionsguide","title":"Configuring GitHub Actions Runners","role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic","kind":"article"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/BlueBubblesGuide":{"title":"Running BlueBubbles iMessage Server","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/bluebubblesguide","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Set up a BlueBubbles iMessage server in a macOS VM — a dramatically simpler alternative to VMware on Windows."}],"role":"collectionGroup","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide","kind":"article","type":"topic"}}}